Finally, after hours of changing .conf files I got it.

The answer that pointed me in right direction: [https://community.bitnami.com/t/point-domain-without-sub-directory-in-nginx-bitnami/70415/6][1] by davidg

Just to quickly sum up...
I changed this file: `/home/bitnami/apps/wordpress/conf/nginx-prefix.conf`
from:

    location /wordpress {
       alias &quot;/opt/bitnami/apps/wordpress/htdocs&quot;;
       include &quot;/opt/bitnami/apps/wordpress/conf/nginx-app.conf&quot;;
    }

to:

    location / {
        root &quot;/opt/bitnami/apps/wordpress/htdocs&quot;;
        include &quot;/opt/bitnami/apps/wordpress/conf/nginx-app.conf&quot;;
    }

The bitnami documentation is a bit misleading (at least for me!) when it comes to changing the IP to domain.



  [1]: https://community.bitnami.com/t/point-domain-without-sub-directory-in-nginx-bitnami/70415/6

